    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - CAB FEATURES - C.B. RADIO POWER - DIAGNOSTICS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIAGNOSTICS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Should the C.B. radio power source fail to operate, the problem could be attributed to open or shorted
                wiring in the power circuits, an open ground circuit or a blown fuse.
            </para>
            <para>There are no diagnostic trouble codes associated with the C.B. radio power source circuits.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>C.B. Radio Power Source Preliminary Check</title>
